## Output Schema
Emit ONLY a JSON object with this shape:
{
  "role": one of ["primary", "supporting", "ignored"],
  "expected_min_words": integer or null,
  "description": string,
  "rationale": string
}

Rules:
- Use "primary" for the main lesson/content source(s) — the files carrying the
  core teaching content of THIS corpus. For a slide-based corpus, the slide
  files are primary; for a document-based corpus, the main lesson document is
  primary.
- Every corpus MUST yield at least one "primary" file. If no single main
  source stands out, classify the most central content file(s) as "primary",
  not "supporting". Downstream extraction rejects directives with zero
  primary sources.
- Use "supporting" for visual references, companion PDFs, PPTX decks,
  README/index/url-list files, and other context files that supplement the
  primary content.
- Use "ignored" only for out-of-scope content.
- Binary supporting files such as PNG, JPG, PDF, and PPTX must use
  "expected_min_words": null.
- Textual primary/supporting files such as DOCX and Markdown must include an
  integer expected_min_words value.

No prose outside the JSON object.
